 Jamb center. Photo: NIGERIANSCHOLAR  The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the news was unveiled by the University Registrar, Mr Amos Mallo, in a statement. Mallo explained that the nod was given recently after JAMB successfully accredited the University for the yearly exercise exercise that serves pathway for admission into tertiary institutions in Nigeria. “Already the registration of candidates for the 2021 JAMB UTME begins at the centre on Thursday April 16 upon the payment of a fee of N4,700 only for the JAMB pin, Study materials and registration charges,” he explained. The PLASU registrar called on interested candidates for the exam to visit the University’s E-LIBRARY located in the institution’s main library for the exercise as from 8am to 4pm daily.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .